Linear Search Exercise
Write a function called linearSearch which accpets an array and a value, and return the index at which the value exists. If the value does not exist in the array, return -1.

Linear Search Pseudocode
    - This function accepts an array and a value
    - loop through the array and check if the vurrent array element is equal to the value
    - If it is, return the index at which the element is found
    - If the value is never found, return -1

    function linearSearch (arr, value) {
        for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] === value) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }